==English==
===Proper noun===
'''Miriam'''

# Sister of Moses and Aaron
# A female given name


===Etymology===
Hebrew: [[מרים|מִרְיָם]] (Miriam), from Aramaic ''[[מרים]]'' (Maryām), bitter, from a root '''מר''' (<small>MR</small>) meaning "to be bitter"; the name corresponds to the Hebrew ''[[מרים]]'' (Miryām), '''[[Miriam]]'''

